```"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Your underlying ViewModel logic is correct: calling `onBeginEditSet(set)` should set `editingSetId = set.id` and `editingNotesText = set.notes`. However, in the UI, the show-textbox condition for notes editing is

```kotlin
isBeingEdited = uiState.editingSetId == set.id && uiState.editingNotesText.isNotBlank()
```

This logic **requires** that the set already has non-empty notes to enter edit mode. If a note is blank (which is common), you **never** enter edit mode, even after a long-press. This is the cause of your bug.

**How to fix:** 
You want to allow editing when either
- (a) This set is being edited (editingSetId == set.id), regardless of .editingNotesText being empty.
So change the logic to:
```kotlin
